  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Before you start cooking, take your<strong> steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>wedges</strong> to a baking tray (or two!), drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and put the tray[s] in the oven for 30 min or until golden</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-hoisin-pork-and-cucumber-pickle/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the wedges are cooking, halve your <strong>cucumber</strong> lengthways, scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon and discard, then finely slice the flesh</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> ginger</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-hoisin-pork-and-cucumber-pickle/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>honey</strong>, <strong>hoisin sauce</strong> and<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>your <strong>five-spice mix</strong> to a large bowl</p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>water</strong> and give everything a good mix up - this is your <strong>marinade</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>pork loin steak[s]</strong> to the marinade and set aside</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-hoisin-pork-and-cucumber-pickle/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>sliced cucumber</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>rice vinegar</strong> in a bowl</p><p>Mix well and set aside – this is your <strong>cucumber pickle</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-hoisin-pork-and-cucumber-pickle/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a hight heat</p><p>Once hot, shake off the excess marinade from the <strong>pork </strong>(you'll use the rest later) and add to the pan</p><p>Cook the pork loin for 5-6 min on each side or until browned and cooked through</p><p>Once done, transfer the<strong> cooked pork</strong> to a clean chopping board or plate (reserve the pan), cover with a tea towel and leave to rest for 5 min</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-hoisin-pork-and-cucumber-pickle/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>marinade</strong> to the reserved pan</p><p>Cook for 3-5 min or until it's approaching a dark, thick and sticky consistency – this is your <strong>glaze</strong></p><p>Tip: The glaze will continue to thicken when it's off the heat</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-hoisin-pork-and-cucumber-pickle/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the<strong> rested pork</strong> finely</p><p>Add any <strong>resting juices</strong> to the glaze</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-hoisin-pork-and-cucumber-pickle/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sliced pork</strong> with the <strong>glaze</strong> drizzled over</p><p>Serve the<strong> potato</strong> <strong>wedges</strong> and <strong>cucumber pickle</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
